  "text": "In the present study, we provide evidence that the systemic activation of TLR2 contributes to mortality in mice subjected to severe cecal ligation and puncture (CLP), a model of acute polymicrobial septic peritonitis [CITATION_1] . We found that TLR2 signaling down-regulated the expression of the chemokine receptor CXCR2 on the surface of circulating neutrophils, impairing migration to the site of infection and affecting disease severity.",
